== Introduction: The Bakery Moment

Have you ever stood in line at a bakery in Brussels, the warm scent of fresh bread filling the air, and mentally rehearsed exactly what you're going to say? You know the words. You've studied the grammar. But when it's your turn, a wave of panic hits. You freeze, just point, or switch to English.

If this sounds familiar, you are not alone. That gap between what you know in your head and what you can say in the moment is where confidence is lost. It's a feeling shared by almost every language learner, including those of us who grew up here and now live abroad.

This guide is designed to bridge that gap. We're not going to drill you on verb conjugations. Instead, we'll focus on the single most important element for speaking a new language: *confidence*. We will give you practical tools, safe scenarios to practice, and a new mindset to help you move from fear to fluency, one small victory at a time.

