=== Scenario 2: Buying Bread at the Bakery (_Boulangerie_)
- *The Goal:* To successfully buy one type of bread.
- *The Location:* Any local bakery.
- *Key Vocabulary:*

#table(
  columns: (1fr, 1.5fr),
  [*French*], [*English*],
  [*Une baguette*], [A baguette (long loaf)],
  [*Un pain gris*], [A whole wheat loaf],
  [*Un pain blanc*], [A white loaf],
  [*Tranché*], [Sliced],
  [*Pas trop cuit(e)*], [Not too well-done/dark],
  [*Bien cuit(e)*], [Well-done/dark],
  [*Et avec ceci ?*], [Anything else with that?],
  [*Non, ce sera tout, merci.*], [No, that will be all, thank you.],
)

- *Sample Dialogue:*
  - *Baker:* Bonjour Madame/Monsieur.
  - *You:* Bonjour. Je voudrais une baguette, s'il vous plaît.
  - *Baker:* Oui. Bien cuite ?
  - *You:* Pas trop cuite, s'il vous plaît.
  - *Baker:* Voilà. Et avec ceci ?
  - *You:* Ce sera tout, merci.
  - *Baker:* Un euro vingt. (1,20€)
  - *You:* (You pay) Merci, au revoir.
  - *Baker:* Merci, bonne journée !

#warning-box[
  *The "Switch":* Sometimes, a local might hear your accent and switch to English to be helpful. This can be discouraging. Have a polite phrase ready: "*Merci, mais je voudrais pratiquer mon français, si possible.*" (Thank you, but I would like to practice my French, if possible.) Most people will happily switch back.
]

